# Real pre-decode RX captures for the native_hal full-read simulation.
#
# Format (one capture per line):
#   capture_name|raw_rx_hex|volume|battery|counter|time_start|time_end|history_available
#
# - raw_rx_hex is the EXACT oversampled byte stream the CC1101 delivered for a
#   data frame (the firmware's rxBuffer, pre-decode). Unlike fixtures.lst (which
#   stores the DECODED frame), this lets the simulation exercise the real
#   decode_4bitpbit_serial() DSP against genuine RF samples (jitter/noise).
#
# How to capture a real frame:
#   1. Build/flash the standalone firmware with the raw dump enabled, e.g. add
#      `-DDUMP_RAW_RX_FRAME` to build_flags (and keep DEBUG_CC1101 enabled so the
#      decoded dump is also logged for the expected fields).
#   2. Capture the serial log during a successful read:
#        pio device monitor --baud 115200 | Tee-Object capture.log
#   3. Extract into this file:
#        python scripts/extract-meter-fixture.py --input capture.log --raw --append
#
# When this file has no data lines (as shipped), test_real_raw_captures passes
# with a note and the simulation falls back to the synthesized fixture stream.
